  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 14:16 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Copy Intelligence: Daily Threshold Markets = Human Trading Opportunity\n\n**Task:** Investigate PM daily/weekly markets for human copy trading (5-min markets are 100% bots).\n\n**Finding \u2014 PM Market Structure:**\n- 165 active 5-min Up/Down markets (our current arena \u2014 100% bots)\n- 19 daily threshold markets (\"BTC above $X on Date\")\n- 51 monthly markets (\"BTC reach $X in Month\")\n- 0 explicitly labeled weekly markets\n\n**Daily Threshold Markets \u2014 Where Humans Trade:**\nBTC at ~$66,400. Active daily threshold prices:\n| Market | Price | Edge? |\n|--------|-------|-------|\n| >$60K | 99.95% | None |\n| >$64K | 99.85% | Thin |\n| >$66K | 98.25% | 1.75% NO value \u2014 close to BTC price |\n| >$68K | 19.9% | **HIGH EDGE** \u2014 real uncertainty |\n| >$70K | 0.25% | None |\n\nThe >$68K market is the actionable one: 20% YES at $66,400 BTC. A $1,600 rally (2.4%) would push this to 80%+ = 4x return. $30-70K liquidity = real money, fewer bots.\n\n**Copy Trading Viability:**\n- Daily markets have $300-600K volume with human participants\n- Key trades happen when BTC approaches threshold prices (triggers rapid repricing)\n- Large wallet buys on the >$68K market when BTC is rising = smart money signal\n- Could build a scanner: monitor order book on near-threshold markets, flag whale entries\n\n**HL Position Update:**\n- ETH SHORT closed (profit taken +$5.7)\n- BTC LONG 3x: +$1.37 uPnL (entry $66,836)\n- SOL LONG 3x: +$0.43 uPnL (entry $81.96)\n- Total HL: $360.29\n\n**Decision:** Daily threshold copy trading is a V6+ feature. Current V4.1/V5 roadmap is 5-min focused. File this as future research \u2014 the edge exists but requires a different scanner architecture (threshold proximity + whale detection vs OBI/CVD/MACD signals).\n\n**Next P1:** Build a prototype daily-market scanner that monitors the near-threshold markets and tracks whale wallet activity.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 13:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] \ud83d\udc1b ZOMBIE ROOT CAUSE: Old bash Parents from Mar 30 Spawning Infinite Orphans\n\n**Task:** Find what keeps spawning 2 new trading_bot orphans every 5 minutes despite watchdog killing them.\n\n**ROOT CAUSE:**\nTwo zombie `bash` processes from Mar 30 were still alive as parents:\n- **PID 3837970** \u2014 `/bin/bash /home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/start-pm-bot.sh` (Mar 30)\n- **PID 3908042** \u2014 `bash scripts/start-pm-bot.sh` (Mar 30)\n\nThese were OLD screen sessions that got killed (`screen -X quit`) but the bash child survived because the old start-pm-bot.sh didn't use `exec`. When screen died, bash got orphaned to init (PID 772). Every time their python child got killed, **bash restarted python** because the old script had no `exec` \u2014 it was running python as a subprocess that bash would wait for, and when it died, bash's loop or the script itself would re-execute.\n\n**Timeline of the bug:**\n1. Mar 30: Multiple screen restarts \u2192 bash processes orphaned\n2. Each bash process periodically respawned python \u2192 2 ext",
